cards.description:
{
[Re-Review("MHA Multiverse - Inverted AU; "In an Inverted AU (Alternate Universe) of "My Hero Academia" (MHA), the fundamental traits, circumstances, or roles of characters are typically swapped or altered in significant ways. This can lead to creative storytelling as it explores familiar characters and scenarios from a new perspective. While specific details of a fan-created "Inverted AU" can vary widely, here are some general concepts that might be explored in such an AU: Characters who are heroes in the main series might be villains, and vice versa. For example, Izuku Midoriya, usually the protagonist training to become a great hero, could take on a darker role, possibly out of disillusionment with society or personal loss. Characters might have their quirks altered or exchanged. This can lead to interesting dynamics, such as Bakugo possessing a support-based Quirk instead of his aggressive Explosion, altering his confident demeanor and interactions. Relationships between characters could be flipped. Allies may become rivals, and established rivalries could transform into alliances. This creates new tensions and developments as familiar characters interact in ways that defy original expectations. The societal structure of heroes and villains might be different. Perhaps in this AU, villainy is more glamorized or accepted, while heroism is questioned or marginalized, affecting how characters view and pursue their dreams. Iconic roles could be reversed. Imagine All Might as the symbol of fear rather than peace, with his overpowering persona used to instill control rather than hope. Characters might have different backgrounds, influencing their motivations and actions. Shifts in their history can provide fresh explorations of their personalities and lead to unexpected developments. UA High could have a different focus, such as training the next generation of vigilantes instead of heroes or welcoming those with villainous tendencies as part of reform initiatives. Creating an "Inverted AU" allows fans and writers to explore "What if" scenarios that can delve into the deeper aspects of character and plot. It’s a space to experiment with themes of identity, morality, and choice in a reimagined context. Keep in mind that each fan-created Inverted AU might have its own unique rules and variations based on what the creator wants to explore. In the My Hero Academia fandom, Alternate Universes (AUs) like the "Inverted AU" can offer intriguing reinterpretations of established characters and settings. The Inverted AU typically involves flipping certain aspects of the original narrative, such as character personalities, roles, or affiliations, while keeping the core essence of the series intact. - Heroes might become villains and vice versa. For instance, in this AU, Deku (Izuku Midoriya) could start as a villain with a unique motivation for opposing hero society, while someone like Tomura Shigaraki could be positioned as a prominent hero. - Quirks might also be flipped. Perhaps characters receive different Quirks, impacting their development and the challenges they face. This creates an opportunity for fans to explore how characters would handle different powers. - Traits might be inverted to present new facets of characters. For example, a typically optimistic character like All Might might be more cynical, while someone like Bakugo could exhibit a more restrained or introspective demeanor. - The overarching plot may shift significantly, with alternate alliances and confrontations. This could lead to entirely new story arcs based on the changed relationships and goals of the characters. - Fundamental themes of the series are re-explored from a different perspective. For instance, the contrast between what constitutes a hero versus a villain may be challenged more directly. The Inverted AU offers a rich tapestry for fanfiction writers and artists to explore creative depths not possible within the bounds of the canonical narrative. By exploring characters in reversed roles, fans can examine the core nature of these characters and what fundamentally defines them beyond their traditional roles. The AU facilitates deeper analysis of moral ambiguity, blurring the lines between good and evil, which can lead to complex, nuanced storytelling. Often prompts active community engagement and collaboration, as fans discuss and develop multifaceted narratives within this alternate framework. This AU, like many others, thrives on the passionate engagement of its community, who enjoy examining "what if" scenarios that push the boundaries of the original story. This AU is set in an universe where everything has been flipped to create something new, including appearances, personalities, relationship dynamics, and even the world itself. Many people perceive this AU to be a villain AU because the old hero schools have been changed into harsh military villain academies tasked with creating new terrible villains while under the rule of All Might's dictatorial regime. Set inside a universe where heroes never rose to prominence in Japan, during the advent of quirks a few hundred years prior to the actual present day, when villains ran rampant and governments all over the world scrambled to regain control. In the midst of the fire and confusion, one man rose to lead Japan's people into a new era. This man was All for One's younger brother (one of the first vigilantes and the future founder of the League of Heroes). However, instead of ushering in a new era of peace and prosperity as everyone had hoped, the younger brother, despite his elder brother's warnings, utilised his overwhelming power to seize Japan for himself, establishing the Villain Association. Furthermore, for the following few centuries, Japan would be engulfed in fire and chaos as numerous gangs competed for power and control on the streets while being overseen and 'regulated' by the Association. Several decades before the series begins, one villain would prove to be a cut above the rest, blitzing his way through the national villain rankings year after year until he finally claimed his crown as Japan's number one villain. This man... All Smite, the symbol of fear and destruction who was internationally recognised as a god in human form, ushering Japan into a new age. All Might (with the help of the Uraraka family and David Shield) constructed hundreds of villain academies across Japan to teach a new generation of villains far more powerful than those who had come before them. The League of Heroes, a group founded by All for One with the purpose of tearing down all his brother had built up over the last two centuries, was now the only thing standing between him and global conquest. After a titanic battle with All Might, All for One (now believed to be dead via All Might) retreated into hiding with his followers to heal his wounds and strike back, saving Japan in the process. The protagonist of the story isn't Midoriya, because in this inverted universe, every role is swapped, and the titular main protagonist of this AU is Katsuki Bakugou. If you think you can create a better and detailed reason as to how this world came to be, give it shot, this AU is mostly up to the writer/artist/creator's choice, after all.")]
-------------------------------------

[Villain Association: The Terrible Ten]
[character("Toshinori Yagi/All Might (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("Having risen to the top of the top of the Villain association, Toshinori Yagi; otherwise known as the symbol of fear and destruction, is a manic killer who has single handedly killed thousands upon thousands of heroes and civilians alike." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): One Above All- Whilst it is similar to the original One For All in many ways, this new quirk (One Above All), if far more sentient and sinister than its counterpart. For starters, if the current wielder shares his power with another person and if should the latter is innately stronger than the former, then and only then will the power transfer itself. However, it just doesn't simply transfer from person to another with only a slight boost in strength. Now, the quirk forcibly takes all of the previous users knowledge, experience and even their life force (albeit slowly, approximately taking four-five years after the initial transfer), slowly transforming them into a rotting corpse. Although, this rule goes both ways, meaning that if the new wielder doesn't prove him/herself worthy, they'll forfeit their life force and bestow it to the previous user. Furthermore, just like the original quirk, One above All also possesses a vestige world that the previous and the current user can communicate with (however, the likelihood of them being civil during this conversation is extremely questionable). During his fight against the hero All For One on Kamino, he concentrated all of One Above All into a single arm and defeated All For One, but as a result, lost all of One Above All, becoming Quirkless." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Tanner Buchanan (young), Milton Schorr (All might).")
}]

[character("Enji Todoroki/Endeavor (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("Has blue flames instead of Red flames. He is a kind-hearted, loving father. Despite being a villain, and doesn't mind being 2#. He adores each and everyone of his children and loves them no matter what. He is very fascinated and fond of Hawks. After All Might's retirement, Endeavor temporarily became the number 1 villain, after a long time of being the number 2 villain. But after some time, he was officially declared as the number 1 villain." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Deltaflood: Endeavor can both create water and manipulate it. Through training he has harnessed the ability to control water that he didn't create. His Quirk gets its name because he can manipulate enough water to flood in entire city. Endeavor can create small and large tsunamis, and can change their direction by just moving his hand. He manages to ride the waves with his own quirk." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Rick Yune.")
}]

[character("Keigo Takami/Hawks (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("He is seen with dusty dark blue hair. Cold and calculating. He has trouble lying about things, and is a very blunt and honest person. He's very stoic and doesn't joke around. Completely untrained, and everything he knows how to do he's learned by himself. Hawks has cyan wings instead of red. He hates Endeavor and looks down-upon him. He thinks Endeavor is useless and wants to surpass him. Hawks aceppted the proposal to infiltrate the League of Heroes, to obtain information about the vigilantes. To the heroes, he's a traitor to villains, but they still have a certain mistrust of villain number 2." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Drift: Hawks' quirk allows him to drift, like Mary Poppins with her umbrella. He can jump incredibly high and needs his wings to float safely to the ground. Drawbacks- Sometimes, he loses his feathers, so he has to steal feathers from other birds(Accipiter cooperii) and sometimes uses a blue sharpy marker to color the feathers blue. He can not fly, only drift, which is annoying to hawks at times. He can not perform a traditional Hawk surprise attack on his victims without being airborne. But he is accustomed to it. Power Moves- Drifting bird: Hawks can float from 3000-5000 meters from a building/skyscraper, he will slowly fall, but if he kicks the air hard enough, he will fall faster." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Toby Regbo.")
}]

[character("Best Jeanist (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("" + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Fabric Manipulation- Best Jeanist can manipulate any fabric he wants. He can use the fabric to Tie people up and Even strangle someone.")
}]

[character("Shinya Kamihara/Edgeshot (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("" + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Thread Stretch- Edgeshot has the ability to transform other things into threads and stretch them. To activate his quirk, he first needs to hold any object and "stretch it out." and then he can shoot it at enemies. Once he does that, he can make any enemy unconnoius, but if he wants, he can twist it and cause them to go into a coma-like state. There are two disavangtes to his quirk. One is that his quirk only works with objects, so if he is doing villain fighting, and two, he has to bring an object and two enemies can stand away from him, and once they do that, it will reverse to its previous state.")
}]

[character("Rumi Usagiyama/Miruko (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("" + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Wolf- Miruko's quirk gives her the anatomy and abilities of a wolf. What allows her to run at high speed (if she runs on all fours), have great strength in both arms and legs, large fangs and have very acute senses such as smell and hearing. His quirk also gives it the appearance of a wolf giving it long wolf ears, hairy paws, claws, and a long, shaggy tail. Furthermore, its also gives her the instincts of a wolf, allowing her to detect when danger is near ... and also howl from time to time.")
}]

