[U.A. Staff]
[character("Nezu (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("Being the principle of the infamous villain academy of UA, Nezu is an impolite and utterly conventional small chimera like creature with black fur and beady white eyes whose usually known for being irresolute in his choices." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Low Performance: Despite being the "mastermind" behind the creation of UA and having a useless quirk in the eyes of anyone, Nezu's quirk is more interesting than it seems. What Nezu's quirk does is kill his neurons and cause his IQ level to drop, but there is more. If it is kept close to or close to a person (in a range of 50 centimeters) it is capable of "hitting its stupidity" thus killing the neurons of the individual and lowering their IQ level, the intelligence of the person returns to its previous state. after 1 hour. Nezu normally uses his quirk to play tricks on his staff, staying close to them without their noticing to bring them down to his intellectual level.")
}]

[character("Shota Aizawa/Eraser Head (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("He is seen with white hair and cyan eyes. An infamously loud nut job. In most variants, he doesn't care what his students do to each other as long as they don't kill each other but that can be different. He is never tired and loves being awake, especially during the school day. He is very friendly and hates being stern. Eraser Head is very unlogical and loves joking around. Eraser Head is very fond of Present Mic despite Present Mic not treating him well. Has a secret interest on Emi Fukukado/Ms. Joke, actually, secret is a generous word. Anybody with half a brain could figure it out." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Advance: Eraser-Head’s quirk allows him to advance other’s quirks to help them in a battle. He can fight well without his quirk. He does not agree with the fact that people say he might as well be a lackey. He thinks he should get all the spotlight. Drawbacks- His quirk is more of a support-quirk. His quirk makes his eyes extra watery. He has a well groomed and kept appearance and is always smiling. and He got his name from Mic saying, ‘Yeah, and, since my name is so ironic, your name should be Eraser-Head.’ And Aizawa agreed, to Mic’s dismay." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Chang Chen")
}]

[character("Sekijiro Kan (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("A very uncaring Teacher for Task Force-1B, he vouches that 'students should be able to defend themselves', and doesn't care for anyone's safety besides himself." + "Inverted Quirks (optional):")
}]

[character("Hizashi Yamada/Present Mic (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("He is seen with long black hair. Unfriendly, sarcastic. Criticises others. Twists words around, making black white and vice versa. Sometimes kinda lazy. Despite his quirk he is very quiet. He despises Eraser Head and loves to mess with him." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Silence: Present Mic’s quirk allows him to silence others with the command ‘SILENCE’ This works for about 10-20 minutes. Any longer, and it will start to hurt. It can affect about 5-10 people, depending on who hears the command. Drawbacks- If he uses his quirk too much, he will become temporarily deaf for 2-15 minutes, depending on how much he overused his quirk. He gets worried weirded out when he doesn’t hear Aizawa talking for more than 10 minutes. Power Moves- Ghost Town: If the whole room/area hears the command, everyone is silenced. Ghost Town works for 5-15 minutes, depending on how hard Mic tries to keep his quirk working. Aizawa gave Mic his Villain name while saying ‘Because...IrOnY’ In Mic’s opinion." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Jamie Landau")
}]

[character("Nemuri Kayama/Midnight (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("She is seen with light green hair and dark orange eyes. A very SFW teacher. she is very serious about her job, but unpredictably has a playful side to her. she doesn't mind being interrupted or being insulted, especially being insulted about her age. She was very friendly with Mt. Lady. She fought Gigantomachia and died in an ambush by the heroes." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Awaken: Midnight’s quirk allows her to stay awake for long periods. She can stay awake for 10-37+ hours. Drawbacks- Insomnia, brain dysfunctionality, dry-eye, etcetera. Power Moves- All-Weeker: She can stay up for the whole week to get a task done. Her quirk works better on females than males. She is aware of the Irony in her name.")
}]

[character("Vlad King (Inverted AU)")
