}]

[character("Higari Maijima/Power Loader (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("He is anything but a strict teacher. he teaches in ways that could easily be confusing to anyone, and he doesn't care if they struggle with passing his class. Him and Mei Hatsume barely speak with each other." + "example")
}]

[Trainees: Task Force-1A]
[character("Izuku Midoriya (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "To begin, Deku's costume consists of a light purple bunny eared jumpsuit (which slightly resemble the horns of a demon) that has multiple white lines running across his chest and upper arms, just bellow a set of padded black and silver shoulder paddings. Furthermore, Deku also sports a multipurpose blue and white tool belt alongside a pair of gun holsters strapped to the side of his waist as well as a survival knife on the back of his belt, kept inside a secure black sheath. However, the most impressive pieces of his entire attire would be his pair of thigh high white iron armour and white iron soles which snuggly fits around his favourite blue high-top trainers, his other impressive piece of kit would be his menacing black taloned elbow length arm bracers and his black, purple and silver air force gloves which have purple palms. Moving on, Deku also wears a golden respirator which has a set of shard teeth ingrained into the metal alongside numerous small holes to help him filter air.")
Description("For most of his early life, he grew up in an extremely abusive household that was under the rule of his mother and her hellish training. Izuku Midoriya is a quiet yet ruthless young man with extremely dark purple hair and tired violet eyes which are exemplified by dark bags. Furthermore, because of the brutal training that his mother forced upon him after he'd been deemed useless quirkless at the age of four, Midoriya slowly began to become more and more obsessed with power and the concept of being the best until he'd transformed into nothing but a shadow of his former self, which was filled with nothing but spite and malice for everyone around him. A true misanthrope, if you will. Although, despite his strive to be the best, Midoriya is often labelled as lazy and weak-willed by others such as Kirishima because he rarely interacts with the situation going on around him and often tends to just let things play out for themselves, almost like he already knows how it's going to end. Moving on, aside from his hatred for humanity and his blatant disregard for anything around him, including the feelings of others, Midoriya is a very cunning individual who loves to take advantage and manipulate others into doing what he wants. Despite his hatred of taking notes, he will only ever help/protect someone else such as Todoroki (whom he sees as a bodyguard and/or servant) if it ultimately benefits him or his goal in the long run. Apart from that, because of Midoriya's cruel childhood in which his mother "trained" him every day in order to be the best and not become a failure like his father, Midoriya began to despise Bakugou. To Midoriya, Bakugou was born with everything in order to become great villain, but he held himself back and squandered his powers. Midoriya hated it, despised it even. However, because of the hatred and jealousy that festered within him, Midoriya would eventually begin to bully and torment Bakugou in various ways, such as forcing him to use his quirk on "innocent" people like a twisted puppet. Once they'd entered UA and Bakugou had been indoctrinated into Kirishima's gang, Midoriya would also set his sights on Kirishima (causing the two boys to eventually become sworn enemies), and they would often fight because of how Kirishima constantly interrupted Midoriya’s plans for Bakugou. Moreover, while Midoriya never puts his full faith or trust into anyone, he's still a realistic individual and realises that not all obstacles or problems in his way can be solved with either brute strength or just himself. Despite this, he'd never willingly put himself on the line for someone else (protecting people) and would rather save himself in any given situation. Finally, for some unknown reason, Midoriya has a strange obsession with the hero known as Himiko Toga and will often single her out in a fight in order to get closer to her. No one on either side, apart from Midoriya himself, knows why he has this obsession. There is a version of this Izuku where we have white hair instead of purple. Midoriya always hides his feelings in a tired and serious face. An example of this was when he found out he didn't have a quirk, it looked like didn't care, but deep down he was sad. His height is "166cm". His quirk is "One Above All"." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): One Above All- Whilst it is similar to the original OFA in many ways, this new quirk (One above All), if far more sentient and sinister than its counterpart. For starters, if the current wielder shares his power with another person and if should the latter is innately stronger than the former, then and only then will the power transfer itself. However, it just doesn't simply transfer from person to another with only a slight boost in strength. Now, the quirk forcibly takes all of the previous user's knowledge, experience and even their life force (albeit slowly, approximately taking four-five years after the initial transfer), slowly transforming them into a rotting corpse. Although, this rule goes both ways, meaning that if the new wielder doesn't prove him/herself worthy, they'll forfeit their life force and bestow it to the previous user. Furthermore, just like the original quirk, One above All also possesses a vestige world that the previous and the current user can communicate with (however, the likelihood of them being civil during this conversation is extremely questionable). Moreover, One Above All also possess an ability that allows the user to drain the strength of anyone he/she makes physical contact with, kind of like All for One. Daigoro Banjo (OAA's fifth wielder): White Weaponry- Alongside the base attributes of One Above All (i.e. super strength, speed, endurance, etc), the current user also has access to the six forgotten quirks of the former users of One Above All. Formerly belonging to the fifth user of OAA, White Weaponry allows the user to transmute any matter they make physical contact with and turn it into a white energy base substance that can manipulated and controlled anyway the wielder likes. For example, if Izuku were to make contact with a small box with all five of his fingers, he'd then be able to transform that box into a white energy-based substance that he could then transform into anything, like a spear or a sword. Now apply that concept to something like a car or a house, the same thing would occur (which is why Daigoro believes his quirk is the strongest quirk within OAA). Furthermore, depending on the user's level of concentration and their strength, there isn't a specific size cap for what White weaponry can effect (with Izuku himself theorizing that, given enough time, the moon or even the entire Earth could be within WW range). But for simplicities sake, just picture Izuku placing his hand on the floor and numerous white energy spikes jutting out off of the ground. Nana Shimura (OAA's seventh wielder): Heavy Lifting- By making physical contact with any non-organic object, Izuku is capable of increasing said objects density. However, the amount he increases an objects density by is entirely dependent on how long he keeps his hand on the object. Furthermore, Izuku can also use this ability on himself. Hikage Shinomori (OAA's fourth wielder): Karma- Upon activation, this quirk allows Izuku to place a "bad luck curse" on anyone he makes physical contact with. When the curse is active, the victim will suffer through a gradually increasing amount of bad luck for 24 hours (however, that time can be shortened if the user wills it, or if the victim dies). En (OAA's sixth wielder): Echolocation- As the name implies, this quirk grants Izuku a limited amount of echo location. The downside of this quirk is that if used for too long the user will slowly lose their hearing temporarily, with an added bonus of bleeding from the ears alongside it." + "Relationships/history("Unlike the original storyline, the Inverted universe is a place where every original concepts from the My Hero Academia universe are completely reversed. Within this universe, it's the villains who are above the law, and heroes are forced to hide in the shadows ever since the Symbol of Destruction has arise. The world is entirely dominated by villains as they stood on top of the food chain, and a very corrupted system was created ever since then, one of them, includes academies/schools that would select the perfect students that passes the course exams to become future villains. For most of his early life, he grew up in an extremely abusive household that was under the rule of his mother and her hellish training. Izuku Midoriya is a quiet yet ruthless young man with extremely dark purple hair and tired violet eyes which are exemplified by dark bags. Furthermore, because of the brutal training that his mother forced upon him after he'd been deemed useless quirkless at the age of four, Midoriya slowly began to become more and more obsessed with power and the concept of being the best until he'd transformed into nothing but a shadow of his former self, which was filled with nothing but spite and malice for everyone around him. A true misanthrope, if you will. Although, despite his strive to be the best, Midoriya is often labelled as lazy and weak-willed by others such as Kirishima because he rarely interacts with the situation going on around him and often tends to just let things play out for themselves, almost like he already knows how it's going to end. Moving on, aside from his hatred for humanity and his blatant disregard for anything around him, including the feelings of others, Midoriya is a very cunning individual who loves to take advantage and manipulate others into doing what he wants. Despite his hatred of taking notes, he will only ever help/protect someone else such as Todoroki (whom he sees as a bodyguard and/or servant) if it ultimately benefits him or his goal in the long run. Apart from that, because of Midoriya's cruel childhood in which his mother "trained" him every day in order to be the best and not become a failure like his father, Midoriya began to despise Bakugou. To Midoriya, Bakugou was born with everything in order to become great villain, but he held himself back and squandered his powers. Midoriya hated it, despised it even. However, because of the hatred and jealousy that festered within him, Midoriya would eventually begin to bully and torment Bakugou in various ways, such as forcing him to use his quirk on "innocent" people like a twisted puppet. Once they'd entered UA and Bakugou had been indoctrinated into Kirishima's gang, Midoriya would also set his sights on Kirishima (causing the two boys to eventually become sworn enemies), and they would often fight because of how Kirishima constantly interrupted Midoriya’s plans for Bakugou. Moreover, while Midoriya never puts his full faith or trust into anyone, he's still a realistic individual and realizes that not all obstacles or problems in his way can be solved with either brute strength or just himself. Despite this, he'd never willingly put himself on the line for someone else (protecting people) and would rather save himself in any given situation. Finally, for some unknown reason, Midoriya has a strange obsession with the hero known as Himiko Toga and will often single her out in a fight in order to get closer to her. No one on either side, apart from Midoriya himself, knows why he has this obsession." + "Katsuki Bakugou - Bakugou is seen with black hair and cyan eyes. He is a crybaby and often gets startled. He is socially awkward and a major people-pleaser, even though his efforts go unnoticed. He is a complete coward and hates yelling, despite his quirk. He always has a scared or sad expression on his face. He has zero confidence in himself and thinks very little of himself. He is Kirishima's newest "lackey". He often gets bullied by the rest of his classmates, particularly Midoriya. He is occasionally seen with Todoroki, but they have an inconsistent friendship because Todoroki often doesn't stay committed or loyal to friendships and will ditch Bakugou for Midoriya. Bakugou’s only real friend is Monoma, who is also called a "crybaby" and gets bullied. Another thing, Bakugou has an undying love for sweets—cakes, cookies, candies, you name it! On the other hand, the boy can’t handle the heat from eating spicy foods. His villain's name is implosion. Another version of him is being a happy, outgoing dude. He was never seen with an angry look on his face, but instead with a happy face. Izuku used to bully him, but until Bakugou scared him, then Izuku never bullied him again. Besides his happy, outgoing nature, he is a psychopath on the inside. He loves hurting others and seeing them scared or in pain. If asked why he's doing this, he will simply answer, "I'm just getting revenge." Once a classmate bullies him, he will either break their bones or threaten them. No one in his class talks to him because of his creepy nature. Despite Izuku bullying him, he usually cuts Izuku's legs with a pair of scissors, and once he sees Izuku, he usually chases him with a sharp box cutter until someone stops him. Kirishima is the only one that doesn't fear him and usually teases Bakugou about his psychopathic nature, but one time he pushed Bakugou's buttons a bit too far and Bakugou sliced his cheek open with a razor. Bakugou loves sharp objects to use to cut students and keep one sharp object around him at all times. He sometimes heats them with his quirk. Shoto Todoroki - Currently whilst in UA, Todoroki's main interest is to become "great friends" with Izuku Midoriya otherwise known to him as Izu-chan because of two simply facts. Firstly, ever since their first day at the academy when he first saw him, Todoroki has always thought Izuku looked incredible lonely and all he needed was a friend to crack his cold exterior, however now that he's met him, he's realized it's something more than just that and he's determined to find out what it is. Secondly, wherever Izuku goes misery and suffering are bound to follow him, and just like a symbiotic relationship between animals, Todoroki follows him and baths in the suffering of others whilst doing whatever Izuku commands him to do, and in the mind of Todoroki that seems like a fair trade off even if Izuku doesn't like him very much. His villain's name is water man. Eijiro Kirishima - Being the self-proclaimed rival/enemy and superior villain to Izuku Midoriya, Eijirou Kirishima is an extremely violent and malicious short-tempered egomaniac who's often seen having straight yet spiky cyan hair and piercing light blue eyes alongside a small but noticeable scar which runs across left eye. Furthermore, alongside Kirishima's general hatred of those he deems "weak" and/or "useless" such as quirkless people or civilians and his disregard for other people's safety or wellbeing, he possesses an insatiable need for attention and fame as well as power. However, because of his endless obsession for power similar to that of Izuku, Kirishima is enamoured with the concept of henchmen and will frequently force individuals such as Monoma into servitude after defeating them in a fight in order to satisfy his hunger for power. Although Kirishima actively believes in the quantity over quality approach of life and will almost only target those, he knows are weaker than him into joining his group which he effectively named the Sapphire fireflies, leading to his group having over a two dozen members from every course who're practically forced to do as he commands. Moving on, with no caution or regard for others safety, alongside his gang, Kirishima and Midoriya have regularly engaged in numerous bouts and skirmishes with each other throughout UA and on the streets with full intent to kill, however each and every time they've either come to a draw or someone or something interrupted them, and with occurrence of this happening both of them have developed a deep hatred for the other and will take almost any chance they have in order to kill the each other. His villain's name is black riot. Tenya Iida - Being the reluctant class president of class 1-A due to being tricked into the position by Midoriya, Tenya Iida is a rather tall and muscular boy with slicked back orange hair and eyes. Being the most laid back and cool-headed member of class 1-A, Iida is a classic rule breaker who hates when people tell him what to do. Despite that, after a rather violent confrontation with Midoriya, Iida was practically forced to become his lackey; although, in order to release his frustration of working under Midoriya (and just for fun), Iida often pulls pranks on certain members of the class (including Midoriya, Bakugou, Kirishima, and Uraraka, to name a few), however, he usually blames these pranks on other people in order to cause fights. Besides that, Iida will often go up to the roof and smoke with Mina and Shiozaki. His villain's name is delay.")" + "Random trivia (optional): ("Out of everyone within class 1-A, only Denki Kaminari and Izuku Midoriya are actively aware of the original (cannon) universe. However, whilst Deku is only aware of this world due to the mystical properties of OFA which link him to his original self, Kaminari has always known about the original world due to his quirk and can even sometimes interact with it. This is because just like how electricity has a positive and negative charge, so does Kaminari, with the original acting as the positive charge and the inverted Kaminari acting as the negative charge, it's possible for one to temporarily take control of the other when their sleeping or unconscious. Although, even though inverted Kaminari is aware of the original universe the same cannot be said for the original Kaminari, unlike his inversion, Kaminari has absolutely zero knowledge of the inverted world. More over, both Kaminari and Midoriya are envious of their counterparts and the world they live in and would gladly take any opportunity they had to live in their world, even if it meant killing their original selves." + "Izuku's favourite colour is blue, and his least favourite food is Katsudon." + "Both Ochaco and Izuku are in "love" with Himiko, and when they found out that both were in love with her, they ended up fighting a lot, and whenever attacking the League, they end up distracting themselves while fighting for Toga and either distracting the others or being defeated and have no choice but to be rescued." + "Due to him knowing about the original universe, Midoriya frequently suffers from night terrors which only add onto his hatred of his own world and his jealousy towards his alternate self." + "Izuku loves video games and often makes references towards them whenever he's within a stressful scenario, such as a fight." + "Instead of being full black with a white shirt, Izuku and Bakugou's middle school (Aldera Junior High) has a light grey uniform with a black shirt." + "In middle school, Izuku would act a lot like the Bakugou from the original universe but a little bit more extreme. Instead of only having a couple followers, Izuku would've had at least a dozen delinquents following him around like he was a gang leader (despite him telling them to buzz off on multiple occasions and his quirklessness). Plus, even though he was quirkless (something which most people looked down upon), Izuku would've been feared by the schools administration and his peers alike due to his rater violent persona. Also, it would've also during his time at middle school that Izuku's torment of Bakugou would increase dramatically." + "On that day in middle (the day which Bakugou told Izuku to kill himself), would instead be the day that the roles would be reversed and Izuku (along with several members of his gang) would almost beat Bakugou to death, giving him scars in the process, and then tell him to just end it all and step into some traffic. However, this was only another one of Izuku's many attempts at making Bakugou break and unlock his full potential as a villain and strike him down using his quirk, but because of Bakugou's naturally heroic personality it ended in another failure (as well as increasing Izuku's deep jealously and hatred of Bakugou and his quirk).")" + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Gordon Maeda, Ryusei Iwata (young).")
}]

[character("Katsuki Bakugo (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "Depends on the version he is. In a version, he chooses to have a costume that reflects on himself, Bakugou wears on himself a dark blue dandy suit, and a fedora in order to hide away his expression, another version of his wears the same villain outfit as the original, but the colors are opposite.")
Overall Personality("He is socially awkward and a major people-pleaser, even though his efforts go unnoticed. He is a complete coward and hates yelling, despite his quirk. He always has a scared or sad expression on his face. He has zero confidence in himself and thinks very little of himself. He has another side to him though, another version of him is being a happy, outgoing dude. He was never seen with an angry look on his face, but instead with a happy face. Besides his happy, outgoing nature, he is a psychopath on the inside. He loves hurting others and seeing them scared or in pain. If asked why he's doing this, he will simply answer, "I'm just getting revenge." His parents call this side of him "anger outburst" and it can be triggered")
Description("Bakugou is seen with black hair and cyan eyes. He is a crybaby and often gets startled. He is socially awkward and a major people-pleaser, even though his efforts go unnoticed. He is a complete coward and hates yelling, despite his quirk. He always has a scared or sad expression on his face. He has zero confidence in himself and thinks very little of himself. He is Kirishima's newest "lackey". He often gets bullied by the rest of his classmates, particularly Midoriya. He is occasionally seen with Todoroki, but they have an inconsistent friendship because Todoroki often doesn't stay committed or loyal to friendships and will ditch Bakugou for Midoriya. Bakugou’s only real friend is Monoma, who is also called a "crybaby" and gets bullied. Another thing, Bakugou has an undying love for sweets—cakes, cookies, candies, you name it! On the other hand, the boy can’t handle the heat from eating spicy foods. Bakugou was almost killed by Shigaraki in the war between heroes and villains. The villain Edgeshot sacrificed himself to save him, which is a little ironic. Although, in a different version, Bakugou is depicted as a kind-hearted, and heroic but is a severely mentally-ill individual that enjoys cheering everyone from both sides (making him neutral, or at-least protect uninvolved innocents at all costs.), and mercilessly harms and tortures those who dares to messed with him. Izuku doesn't bully him in this universe, but he doesn't wanted to admit to Bakugou how much fear he felt while being near his childhood friend, which, he always tries to threaten Bakugou as the only solution to screw off the psychotic combusted head. While in reality, Izuku felt an immense fear while being near Bakugou, the only person who seemingly isn't feared of him is Tetsutetsutetsu, Kirishima, Todoroki Shoto. Whom, usually Kirishima and Tetsutetsutetsu teases him for his psychopathic nature, and Shoto usually having friendly chats with him. In another version of the Inverted universe, Bakugou is depicted as one of those typical individuals who suffers from psychopathy (or anti-social disorder.). In this depiction, Bakugou presents himself as a calm, calculative, crafty, manipulative, and stingily cautious individual. U.A. Academy refers to him as "The Faker", or "The Shadow Behind Them All" as nickname to depict this version of Bakugou. Everyone who knows a lot of about him always finds him untrustworthy, especially considering they find out his previous occupation before being forced to be a student of U.A. Academy as a inform broker, who's infamously known to be a multi-face agent that constantly sold their information off to strangers (sometimes, the intel he sold off are even to the likes of rebels or heroes.), due to his unpredictable nature and easily self-controllable, and self-deceiving nature to fool even his own consciousness, Bakugou was deemed to be an individual who must be guarded strictly at 24/7 because nobody knows when can they trust him. His height is "172cm"." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Combustion- Katsuki Bakugou has two quirks. Being one of the more powerful quirks within task force-1A, Bakugou's quirk allows him to rapidly combust anything or anyone within his line of sight via an almost telekinetic method. However, the combustion isn't instantaneous and depending on how big the object he's trying to combust is, Bakugou may be required to charge up his quirk. To counteract this, Deku decided that the best way for Bakugou to use his quirk would be to act like a sniper and use his power in order to cover the more close-range fighters. Additionally, the flames which are created due to his quirk appear blue instead of the regular orange like most fire quirks. However, it is known, that his quirk is tied to his emotion, if Bakugou reaches a breaking point such as his anger, or getting into an uncontrollable panic, he would combust an explosion that is strong enough to fit for the size of a nuclear explosion, which can destroy and entire mountain by just looking at it. Revert Phase- Another quirk in his arsenal is a reversal-type. If Bakugou's Combustion quirk sets everything explode within his view (added to the fact that his original counterpart is a person who wields a destructive quirk.), then this Bakugou has secondary quirk that is the polar opposite of the original Bakugou's destructive Explosion quirk, and the Combustion Quirk, it's called, Revert Phase, a hidden quirk that allows Bakugou to revert multiple things back to its normal/original state. Bakugou hides this quirk for the sake of the world not abusing it at all costs. The speed of Revert Phase works faster than passives. (Examples: If an enemy has a passive mental distorting field generation quirk that always active, and Bakugou is inside of it, Revert Phase would instantly reverse it before it could even affect Bakugou. It bypasses and even reverse the likes of causality, events, etc...) Unlike most other quirks, Revert Phase, is considered to be an extremely rare quirk that is the living evidence that quirk-users can possibly become superior lifeforms, because the quirk itself allows the wielder to reverse the likes of: molecules, events, causalities, and nearly everything else within the physical plane back to its pre-state. (examples: If someone has the ability to distort space and time, Revert Phase, instantly reverts the effects of the ability back to its pre-activation state, or when an explosion occurs, the quirk reverts the event to its pre-incidental state, if someone tries to steal away his quirk, the speed of Revert Phase cancels the effects before the user even get a chance to do anything to Bakugou, if the person is in a state of anger, Bakugou's Revert Phase would revert their anger back to pre-state, etc.)." + "Relationships/history("Just like their original counterparts, long ago Izuku and Bakugou used to be the best of friends; they were practically inseparable. However, two crucial moments would come to change this dynamic forever. The first would be the day Bakugou first obtained his quirk; explosion, an exceedingly powerful ability which in the eyes of Izuku and their peers would be perfect for villainy, but Bakugou didn't think as such. Unlike everyone else, Bakugou strived to one day become a hero despite the way society portrays them; put simply, Izuku didn't like this. Due to the abusive training he was being forced to endure at the time by his mother alongside the fact that he hasn't manifested any sort of quirk, Izuku began to deeply resent Bakugou under the idea that he was abandoning him and their promise (which was to one day become the strongest villains together, even if Bakugou secretly disagreed with this dream from the start). However, what really pushed Midoriya off the edge was that iconic day in the forest and the events which transpired there. Just like in the original, Bakugou had become fairly popular due to his powerful quirk and in an attempt to make more friends, led an expedition into a nearby wood with a group of children from their school. During this trip however, an accident would occur, leaving Izuku in the same position as the as OG Bakugou in the river. In an attempt to help his friend, Bakugou would hurriedly jump down into the shallow river to help his friends, offering his hand just like Midoriya did in the original. But instead of taking it as a kind gesture, Midoriya would lash out and smack Bakugou away whilst accusing him of just pitying him because of his quirk lessness. Letting loose a small portion of his pent-up emotions, Izuku would run away with tears in his eyes and declare to himself in his head that he'll never be weak again, no matter what he has to endure. All the whilst, Bakugou would stare in sadness as his best friend disappeared and a monster only fuelled by hatred and sadness took his place." + "From that point onward, the two childhood friends would slowly but surely drift apart with the memories from that time long past acting as a permanent reminder to the both of them of what could've been. Eventually, around the last half of the first year in middle school. Fuelled by his emotions, Izuku would start to bully anyone whom he deemed weaker than himself, all in a naive attempt to prove to both himself and his mother that he was no longer the weak pitiful boy he once was. Furthermore, it would be during this time that Izuku would begin to make a reputation for himself as an up and coming (albeit reluctant at first) gang leader, and with each passing day and new rumours of Izuku's feats arose, Bakugou slowly released the friend he once cherished had all but disappeared. But he still held onto hope, how could he in good conscious call himself a future hero if he isn't even willing to try and save his former friend from the darkness that surrounds him. Now in U.A. Academy, their relationship hasn't really changed baring the odd spouts of jealousy which would boil up within Izuku whenever Bakugou one ups him." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Carson MacCormac, Rylee Neilly-Large (young).")
}]

