Description("He is seen with dark blue hair, with a white lighting streak and dark blue eyes. He is sarcastic, intelligent, emotionally manipulative and a stateful individual. Despite having no interest in females, they find him quite attractive to which; he uses to his advantage. Unlike his opposite, he is extremely good at flirting and can make most woman fall for him. He'll always eventually get back with those who have a debt to him. He despises Jiro and will use any chance to make her feel like a retared. His villain's name is "Shock Therapist"." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Negative Electrokinesis- Upon said quirks activation, Kaminari is capable of manipulating and shaping any and all electricity around him (even if it's created via a quirk). Paired with his sharp battle intuition and intelligence, with his quirk Kaminari is capable of creating and using advanced skills such as electrokinetic flight/surfing via using any surrounding magnetic material or even creating city wide blackouts. His quirk also allows his IQ to grow but once the electricity goes down, he returns to his normal IQ (When his quirk is activated, the electricity Kaminari is controlling appears either light blue or black). However, since Kaminari lives in an Inverted/reverse universe, his electrokinesis is similar to Shigaraki's quirk, it was applied with reverse laws, Kaminari's bolts are made of pure anti-matters, in which, those who are hit by the bolt would end up being disintegrated into nothing but dust. The bolt is also capable of shredding space and time if he focuses on creating a powerful one. This is one of the few rare conditions that chances of obtaining it would be 0.0000000000000001%, this condition same happens to Monoma, Togaru, Kota, and Katsuki Bakugou, it's a condition in which a quirk would eventually reach a level of evolution that it achieves abstract/conceptual affecting abilities. In Kaminari's case, his eletrockinesis grants him the power to summon or disperse lightning bolts that are made out of pure anti-matters." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Sam Jellie.")
