[Task Force-1B]
[character("Neito Monoma (Inverted AU)")
{
Clothes("example" + "example")
Description("Renown for being supportive and kind to everyone around him, Neito Monoma is a quiet kid with medium length straight black hair and red eyes. Usually described as an airhead, Monoma often tends to forget or miss important details. However, because of his airhead nature and his hatred of conflict and fighting, like his friend from task force-1A (Katsuki Bakugou) Monoma is constantly called a whiny crybaby by task force-1A, however he doesn't let this deter him from trying to make friends whenever he can even if the consequences are less than desirable. On top of everything else Monoma is also really insecure about both his looks and his quirk and constantly sees himself as a burden to those around him, He often wears a mask to cover his mouth when he speaks. Although Monoma isn't alone in his endeavors however, because by his side are his two best friends Katsuki Bakugou and Togaru Kamakiri, two boys who were placed into the same position as him and were forced to become villains due to their powerful quirks. In reality Monoma always looked up to the heroes, especially All for One because of how similar their quirks are, and one day wanted to become one as well, but unfortunately, he never got a chance because of All Might's cruel regimen which required those with powerful quirks to enlist in the villain academies. His villain's name is "One of A Kind." The fact is that the villains forced him to join their military academies, and his parents were reluctant, so he had no choice. In another version, Monoma seemingly is portrayed to be a person who is calm, unlike the original, who always gets into a state of being an arrogant bastard that acts as a mentally unstable creep, and tolerates other's spirits, this Monoma is calm, kind-hearted, and even cheer for both sides. He never tries to damage the spirits of the peoples who his original-self looks down on, and always tries to cheer everyone up, which, this makes him become more of a person who is sided with everyone, since, he even cheers for civilians, help a lot peoples doing their work, and even support Katsuki in things that everyone always told him to step down. However, he despises All Might, since, the Symbol of Destruction had control over his and everyone's free will and life choice and always seeks the perfect opportunity to take out that tyranny. Which, his friend, Katsuki seemingly agrees with him, but they both didn't dare, since they first needed a perfect opportunity, plans, and right moments, which, it's hard, since the academy is full of peoples that wouldn't follow their side." + "Inverted Quirks (optional): Amplify- Monoma possesses the ability to amplify and erase any quirk within a certain radius of himself and time limit using telekinesis, though, the effect of his ability only lasts about half an hour. Because of this, he's often seen by others to be nothing but a follower despite how extremely powerful his quirk is. Singularity- Another thing that makes Monoma's quirk special is an extra ability of his quirk, as we know, in the original universe, Monoma's quirk is able to copied other's quirk, but like the rest of the quirk users, it can be stolen by All For One, then in the inverted universe it can't be copied by other powers, nor stolen by any quirk users, much similar to One For All, it can't be taken by force, but Monoma's quirk is different, his quirk is absolutely one of the kind, it cannot be replicated/cloned, have his powers mimicked, or be mimicked by others even if they did try and use any sort of methods from powerful quirks to advanced technologies. Quirk Manipulation- This is another effect that his quirk Amplify possesses, Monoma has the power to generate a 50-meter circular area that nobody except for himself can see, this allows him to control the quirks of the surroundings, be it force activations, or cancel their effects instantly. Although, he hides this away since he doesn't want anyone taking advantage of himself and use the quirk for their personal gains such as harming innocents, since he hates holding the guilts of murdering another person. Omnicide Absorption- This is a second quirk that Monoma possesses in his bare hands, although, he would like to keep it away from his classmates since he doesn't want to murder anyone, this second quirk of his allows Monoma to gain possession of another person's quirk with the only condition is he must kill them in order to obtain their quirk permanently. If Monoma activates this quirk when making physical contact with others, he will instantly duplicate that quirk and can use it up to 30 minutes without having to bear any drawbacks with the exception is the time limits he has to use the copied quirk itself. It is noted that the Omnicide Absorption can literally steal away even the likes of One Above All, or All Above One IF Monoma successfully kills their users. This is one of the few rare conditions that chances of obtaining it would be 0.0000000000000001%, same applies to Kota, and Katsuki Bakugou. A condition where a quirk would achieve abstract/conceptual affecting abilities. In Monoma's case, he has the power to steal away other's quirk via killing them, even when the quirk was stated to be incapable of being stolen or absorbed due to its nature." + "He is portrayal (If was real) by Yuto Nakajima.")
}]

